The '''2011 [[Pacific Games]]''' (officially known as '''NC 2011''') took place in [[Nouméa]], [[New Caledonia]], from August 27 to September 10, 2011. Nouméa was the 14th host of the [[Pacific Games]].<ref name="nc2011"/> Upon closure of the registration for entries, "some 4,300 athletes" had registered from the twenty-two competing nations, although it was expected that not all would attend.<ref name="saipantribune1"/>

==Competing nations==
There were 22 nations from the Pacific competing in Nouméa. The numbers provided in brackets indicate the number of registered athletes prior to the Games, with that number expected to diminish by the Games' start.<ref name="saipantribune1"/><ref name="athlete-list"/> Clicking on the number will take you to a page on that nation's delegation to the 2011 Games.

