'''Djama Robleh''' (born December 31, 1958) is a retired [[Djibouti]]an long-distance runner who specialized in the [[marathon race]].
He won the silver medal in this event at the [[1982 African Championships in Athletics|1982 African Championships]]<ref>[http://www.gbrathletics.co.uk/ic/afc.htm African Championships] - GBR Athletics</ref> and finished eighth in the [[Athletics at the 1984 Summer Olympics - Men's Marathon|marathon]] at the [[1984 Summer Olympics]].<ref>[http://users.skynet.be/hermandw/olymp/ssathm42.html#1984 Athletics - Men's Marathon] (Full Olympians)</ref> In addition he placed 47th at the [[1983 World Championships in Athletics|1983 World Championships]]<ref>[http://www.iaaf.org/WCH05/history/Year=1983/EventCode=3/gender=M/discipline=MAR/combCode=hash/roundCode=f/index.html 1983 World Championships Results - Marathon - Men - Final]</ref> and entered the [[1987 World Championships in Athletics|1987 World Championships]] without finishing the race.<ref>[http://www.iaaf.org/WCH05/history/Year=1987/EventCode=4/gender=M/discipline=MAR/combCode=hash/roundCode=f/index.html 1987 World Championships Results - Marathon - Men - Final]</ref>
His personal best time was 2:08:08 hours achieved in October 1985 in [[Chicago]]. The current Djiboutian record is held by [[Hussein Ahmed Salah|Ahmed Salah]] with 2:07:07 hours.<ref>[http://www.athlerecords.net/Records/AFRIQUE/PLEINAIR/RECDJIBOUTI.txt Djiboutian athletics records] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070608102447/http://www.athlerecords.net/Records/AFRIQUE/PLEINAIR/RECDJIBOUTI.txt |date=June 8, 2007 }}</ref>
