{{Infobox venue | name = Pakruojis Stadium | image = [[File:Pakruojo Stadionas.jpg|250px]] | caption = '''[[UEFA stadium categories|UEFA Category 1 stadium]]''' | fullname = Pakruojis City Stadium | address = Stadiono g. 1 | location = [[Pakruojis]], [[Lithuania]] | coordinates = {{coord|55|58|57.0|N|23|51|53.5|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | built = 1989 | renovated = | expanded = 2010 | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Pakruojis District Municipality]] | operator = | surface = Grass | scoreboard = | construction_cost = | suites = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 2,000 | record_attendance = | dimensions = | tenants = [[FC Pakruojis]] ([[I Lyga]]) }}
'''Pakruojis City Stadium''' is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Pakruojis]], [[Lithuania]]. It opened in 1989 and is used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches.<ref>{{cite news|title=Lietuvos futbolo stadionai|url=http://futbolas.biz/2010/03/20/lietuvos-futbolo-stadionai/|publisher=futbolas.biz|accessdate=15 August 2016|language=Lithuanian}}</ref> It is the home arena for [[FC Pakruojis]] and former [[A Lyga]] club [[FK Kruoja Pakruojis|FK Kruoja]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Pakruojo miesto stadionas|url=http://www.fkkruoja.lt/index.php/k2-tags/2015-m-sezonas/stadionas|publisher=FK Kruoja|accessdate=15 August 2016|language=Lithuanian}}</ref>
In 2010 stadium was renovated.<ref>{{cite news|title=Pakruojyje atidaromas rekonstruotas stadionas|url=http://www.delfi.lt/sportas/futbolas/pakruojyje-atidaromas-rekonstruotas-stadionas.d?id=34984289|publisher=delfi.lt|date=30 July 2010|accessdate=15 August 2016|language=Lithuanian}}</ref> Capacity was increased to 2,000 seats, new technical area added. It currently holds 1st [[UEFA stadium categories|UEFA stadiums]] category.
