[[Category:FC Pakruojis]] [[Category:Sport in Pakruojis]] [[Category:Football venues in Lithuania]] [[Category:Buildings and structures in Šiauliai County]] [[Category:Multi-purpose stadiums in Lithuania]] [[Category:Sports venues completed in 1989]]

'''The Amsterdam Sports Award''' is an award designed by Jos Wong Lun Hing who was born in [[Roermond]], the Netherlands.<ref name="pdf">{{cite web|url=http://www.dmo.amsterdam.nl/contents/pages/77460/brochureamsterdamsportsaward.pdf?iprox_view=dmo|title=The Amsterdam Sports Award|accessdate=April 12, 2010}}</ref> The award which has been around since 1992 is issued by the municipality to the winner or the most valuable member of a leading international professional sport event in [[Amsterdam]].<ref name="Award">{{cite web|url=http://www.dmo.amsterdam.nl/sport/overig/nieuwsartikelen?ActItmIdt=110378|title=The Amsterdam Sports Award uitgereikt aan Gert-Jan Bruggink|date=January 29, 2008|accessdate=April 12, 2010|language=nl}}</ref>
The award are handed out up to a maximum of five times a year. Among the award winners are World and [[Olympic Games|Olympic]] Champions.<ref name="pdf"/> The Amsterdam Sports Award was previously presented to great athletes like [[Alina Kozich]] (2004), [[Haile Gebrselassie]] (2005), [[Anky van Grunsven]], [[Edwin van der Sar]] (2006), [[IJsbrand Chardon]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dmo.amsterdam.nl/sport/overig/nieuwsartikelen?ActItmIdt=88031|title=Sportprijs uitgereikt aan Kamiel Maase|date=October 22, 2007|accessdate=April 12, 2010|language=nl}}</ref> and [[Kamiel Maase]] (2007).<ref name="Award"/>
