{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Eimskipsvöllurinn | nickname = | image = | fullname = | location = [[Reykjavík]], [[Iceland]] | coordinates = {{coord|64|8|36.92|N|21|52|33.64|W|type:landmark|display=inline}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Knattspyrnufélagið Þróttur|Þróttur Reykjavík]] | operator = [[Knattspyrnufélagið Þróttur|Þróttur Reykjavík]] | surface = [[Artificial turf|Artificial grass]] | construction_cost = | architect = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor= | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = Þróttarvöllur | tenants = [[Knattspyrnufélagið Þróttur|Þróttur Reykjavík]] | seating_capacity = 5,478 | dimensions = }}
'''Valbjarnarvöllur''', also known as '''Eimskipsvöllurinn'''<ref name="Sponsorship">{{cite web |url=http://www.fotbolti.net/fullStory.php?id=221234 |title=Heimavöllur Þróttar R. verður Eimskipsvöllurinn |trans-title=The home run out R. will Eimskip course |first=Guðmundur Aðalsteinn |last=Ásgeirsson |publisher=Fótbolti.net |date=22 December 2016 |accessdate=8 February 2017}}</ref> for sponsorship reasons, is a football [[stadium]] in [[Reykjavík]], [[Iceland]]. It is the home stadium of [[Knattspyrnufélagið Þróttur|Þróttur Reykjavík]] who play in the [[Úrvalsdeild]]. The stadium has a capacity of 5,478 fans.
In December 2016, Þróttur Reykjavík announced a three-year sponsorship deal with local [[Freight transport#Ship|shipping]] company [[Eimskipafélag Íslands|Eimskip]] until 2019, which would see the stadium name changed to Eimskipsvöllurinn for the duration of the deal.<ref name="Sponsorship"/>
